## Save Policy (Founder Controls When to Persist)

**Discussion ≠ Save.** Talking about the idea does NOT write to files automatically.

| Founder says | AI does |
|--------------|---------|
| Discuss / brainstorm only | Chat only — no file edits |
| "save" / "save karo" / "save kar do" | Save all discussed-but-unsaved content to vision files |
| "save [part]" / e.g. "save monetization" | Update ONLY that section in `PRODUCT_VISION.md` + rule summary if needed + plan tracker |
| "edit [part]" / change idea | Discuss the change in chat; persist only when founder says save |
| "save all" | Full sync: `PRODUCT_VISION.md` + this rule + plan file |

After any save:
1. Update `PRODUCT_VISION.md` (full or partial section)
2. Update short summary in this rule (if one-liner or key decisions changed)
3. Append to decisions log in plan file + `PRODUCT_VISION.md` changelog
4. If roadmap priorities shift, propose realign to `ROADMAP.md` — do not auto-edit without founder approval

